SUPLINF.P:
On December 20, 2018, the 2018 Farm Bill (Pub. L. 115-334) was signed into law (see 
https://www.congress.gov/bill/115th-congress/house-bill/2/text
). The Secretary of Agriculture and the respective USDA agencies, including, but not limited to FSA, NRCS, and RMA, are working to implement the provisions of the 2018 Farm Bill as expeditiously as possible to meet the needs of producers and other stakeholders. To allow for customer input and ensure transparency, it is important to hear from stakeholders regarding their priorities, concerns, and requests.
